<Window xmlns="https://github.com/avaloniaui"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        Title="Sandbox Modal Demo"
        x:Class="Consolonia.Sandbox.MainWindow">
    <StackPanel HorizontalAlignment="Center"
                VerticalAlignment="Center"
                Spacing="1">
        <TextBlock xml:space="preserve"
                   TextWrapping="Wrap">
Consolonia.Modal provides a mechanism for displaying modal dialogs in Consolonia applications.
Features:
- Modal Overlay: Shades the background to prevent interaction.
- Integration: Use ModalTheme to enable modal support for all windows.
- Customization: Control title, icon, close button visibility.
- Keyboard: Supports Escape key for closing (CancelOnEscape).
- Layout: Position modals with HorizontalAlignment and VerticalAlignment.
- Themes: Supports Modern and TurboVision themes.

Detailed Layout:
- First Child: Its size determines the modal box size.
- Stretch: First child must have HorizontalAlignment/VerticalAlignment as Stretch.
- Positioning: Set Margin, Alignment, or size on ModalWindow to position the frame.

Mechanics:
- ModalHost: Every Window gets a ModalHost when ModalTheme is active.
- ShowModalAsync: Use this method from code-behind to display the modal.
</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock Text="Welcome to Consolonia Modal Sandbox!"
                   HorizontalAlignment="Center" />
        <Button Content="Show Modal"
                Click="OnShowModalClick"
                HorizontalAlignment="Center" />
    </StackPanel>
</Window>